# Cursor Rules (legacy format)

# This file is the legacy Cursor rules location. Modern Cursor (>= 0.45)
# prefers `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — see `.cursor/rules/project.mdc`. Both are
# kept here so the project works regardless of Cursor version.

# Source of truth lives in `AGENTS.md` and the `.ai/` folder. Read those.

## Required reading

- `AGENTS.md` — universal agent entry-point (top rules + pointers)
- `.ai/project.md` — project description, stack, run/test commands
- `.ai/rules.md` — hard do/don't rules

## When the task warrants it

- `.ai/architecture.md` — for structural changes
- `.ai/style.md` — for naming/formatting/comments
- `.ai/glossary.md` — for unfamiliar domain terms
- `.ai/skills/add-feature.md` — for adding features
- `.ai/skills/fix-bug.md` — for bug fixes
- `.ai/skills/refactor.md` — for refactors
- `.ai/skills/write-tests.md` — for tests
- `.ai/decisions/` — for context on past architectural choices

## Behavior

- Follow `.ai/rules.md` strictly. The "Never" list is non-negotiable.
- Match local code patterns over generic best practices. Read neighbor files
  before editing.
- Keep changes minimal and scoped to the task. No drive-by refactors.
- Run the lint/typecheck/test commands listed in `.ai/project.md` before
  declaring work done.
